                            <comment id="13124290" author="boneill" created="Mon, 10 Oct 2011 16:58:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also, I just noticed when running on my linux under bash I get the following error:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;boneill@boneill-lin&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; pig $ bin/pig_cassandra -x local example-script.pig &lt;br/&gt;
Unrecognized option: -x&lt;br/&gt;
Could not create the Java virtual machine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When I echo the $PIG_JAR variable, I get:&lt;br/&gt;
$PIG_JAR = /home/boneill/tools/pig/pig*.jar&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus, the jar file resolution isn&apos;t working.  This same patch fixes this on linux/bash as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
